4‑day plan
Day 1 – Jobs (core of the app)
Backend logic

Implement JobService (IJobService) using:
Entities: Job, Organization
DTOs: CreateJobDto, UpdateJobDto, JobResponseDto
Filter: JobFilter + PagedRequest / PagedResult<JobResponseDto>
Response<T> wrapper.
Map properties manually or via AutoMapper (if you want to use it).
API

Create JobsController:
POST /api/jobs – create job ([Authorize(Roles = "Organization")]).
GET /api/jobs/{id} – get by id.
GET /api/jobs – paged list with JobFilter (query params).
PUT /api/jobs/{id} – update (Organization or Admin).
DELETE /api/jobs/{id} – delete (Admin or Org owner).
Extra: GET /api/jobs/by-organization/{orgId}, GET /api/jobs/search?title=....
Wire DI: register IJobService → JobService.
Check

Use Swagger:
Login as Organization.
Create job, list jobs, update, delete.
Day 2 – Job applications (apply to jobs)
Backend logic

Implement JobApplicationService (IJobApplicationService) using:
Entity: JobApplication
DTOs: CreateJobApplicationDto, UpdateJobApplicationDto, JobApplicationDto, JobApplicationResponseDto
Filter: JobApplicationFilter
Business rules:
A Candidate can apply only once per job.
Default ApplicationStatus = Pending.
API

Create JobApplicationsController:
POST /api/job-applications – apply to job (Candidate).
GET /api/job-applications/{id} – get by id.
GET /api/job-applications – paged list (Admin).
GET /api/job-applications/by-user/{userId} – Candidate’s applications.
GET /api/job-applications/by-job/{jobId} – Organization’s job applications.
PUT /api/job-applications/{id}/status – change status (Organization/Admin).
DELETE /api/job-applications/{id} – cancel/delete.
Check

In Swagger:
Candidate: apply.
Org: see applicants for their job, change status.
